Appeals are most often made after a trial or final decision in a case, but an appeal can also occur before a final decision.

Defendant Violet Star Reynolds in court with attorney Shirlene Renee Perrin.  Defendant in custody.  William Lund Norine appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Discussion regarding progression today for cases.  DA recited agreement of State caping their sentence recommendation to 20 years (5 ys. Confinement and 15 yr. E.S. and a fine of $2,000 plus costs; As to 14CF188 the Court sentenced the def. to 25 yrs. initial confinement w/15 yr. E.S., plus a fine of $20,000 plus costs.  All sentences run consecutive to each other.  Conditions of extended supervision; 1)  Absolute sobriety; 2) No possession of firearms; 3) Follow the recommendation and treatment plans deemed appropriate from an assessment or as determined by your agent; 4) Take all medications as prescribed; 5) Lifetime registry as a sex offender and comply with sex offender registry and laws; 6) No abusive contact with Ruth Chavarria; 7) No contact with ABL or JLC; 8) No contact with anyone convicted of a felony drug offense or a sexual crime conviction or anyone on community supervision without agent approval; 9) Engage in a sex offender treatment program; 10) Engage in alcohol or drug abuse treatment programs; 11)  Internet and social media restrictions as deemed appropriate by agent; 12) No contact with minors without agent approval; 13) No contact with James Hedberg or Shelly Gonzales; Court orders restitution in 14CM188 in the amount of 246.64, in 16CF35 restitution is ordered in the amount of $120, in 16CF90 restitution is ordered in the amount of $130.  Jail credit to apply; DNA ordered in all cases upon conviction.
